What you need to know:

According to police reports, seven people were arrested during the raid, including three officers working with the Presidential Escort Unit.Uasin Gishu police boss Johnston Ipara said Mr Sudi's allies helped “fish” him from his hideouts, but the officer could not explain how the MP managed to hide in suspected plain-sight.Even though they are yet to establish where the legislator was hiding, Mr Ipara said, police suspect he was in Nandi County.